OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FCanada's Supreme Court     
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Fupholds C$9m fine on maple 
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5Fsyrup thief                
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, Canada's top court has imposed a C$9.1m
OL,6, ($7.3m; #5.5m) fine on a man behind one
OL,7, of the country's stickiest crimes - the
OL,8, theft of 3,000 tonnes of maple syrup.  
OL,10,FThe so-called Great Canadian Maple     
OL,11,FSyrup Heist saw the loss of nearly     
OL,12,FC$18m worth of syrup from the country's
OL,13,Freserves by a group of thieves.        
OL,15,FThe court ordered Richard Vallieres, a 
OL,16,F"major player" in the scheme, to pay a 
OL,17,Fpenalty or face six years in prison.   
OL,19,FVallieres was found guilty in 2016 of  
OL,20,Ffraud, trafficking and theft.          
